<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n05119j"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n05" href="#n05119j">N05 (VI.B.2)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n05all.htm#n05119j"> 119(j)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> boiling act <small>Red</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n05119j"> <li>FW unlocated</li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">Henry <font color="green">[VIII]</font> is computed to have put 72,000 persons to death. There was only one step from the lash and the branding iron to the gallows and disembowelment and he even enacted a <mark>Boiling Act</mark> under which people were boiled alive at Smithfield. <small> Benedict Fitzpatrick, <a name="IIMB" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#IIMB"><cite title="source">Ireland and the Making of Britain</cite></a> (1922) 299</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
